race.comment: ELENA MONTERO (7) resumed 50 days ago at Kilmore well supported and missed by 2L. She's won a Seymour jumpout since and is still well shy of her best city form. The inside barrier will advantage and she will be hard to beat at this level. RUBIQUITY (8) resumes and has raced well in town in stronger than this. He's won fresh and looked on song in a Terang jumpout a month ago. Maps for the run of the race, and Coffey is engaged. A solid each-way chance. DAMAS (2) is in a smart barn and has been well prepared for her return. Has a soft gate and 1,5kg claim and is likely to come back better. Keep well onside. SURPRISATIC (9) was backed off the map when winning his Maiden by a space at Mildura. Had switched back to the Stanley yard and has been kept on the fresh side.  He's still well shy of his best and despite the wide gate and the tougher grade, keep onside.
